issue.title: Recording UI appears after 3 seconds
issue.body:
<!--
Thank you for helping us test Kap. Your feedback helps us make Kap better for everyone!

Before you continue; please make sure you've searched our existing issues to avoid duplicates. When you're ready to open a new issue, include as much information as possible. You can use the handy template below for bug reports.

Step to reproduce:    If applicable, provide steps to reproduce the issue you're having.
Current behavior:     A description of how Kap is currently behaving.
Expected behavior:    How you expected Kap to behave.
Workaround:           A workaround for the issue if you've found on. (this will help others experiencing the same issue!)
-->

**macOS version:**    Monterey (12)
**Kap version:**      3.5.2

#### Steps to reproduce
1. Start Kap
2. Click Kap's icon in the top bar to start a recording

#### Current behavior
Kap's recording UI appears after 3 seconds, sometimes more. 

#### Expected behavior
Kap's recording UI to appear in less than 300ms

#### Workaround
It looks like I can draw the recording box before the UI appears

<!-- If you have additional information, enter it below. -->
M1 Max 64gb, macOS 12.1

Update: Unfortunately, 3.5.3 did not solve the problem for me. I also made sure to use the M1 binary.

comment.body: I've noticed having an extra monitor increases the time to load substantially.

issue.title: Mac Support
issue.body:
I can see from [the README](https://github.com/infamousjoeg/pyaim#macos) and a search through the issues that there is no support for Mac yet and I'm wondering **why** that is? 

Is there a big thing making it hard to have Mac support, or has there just not been sufficient interest yet?

**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I'd like to get passwords when my script is run on a Mac, but Mac doesn't appear to be supported.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
To be able get passwords when the script is run a Mac, just like the other platforms.

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
Rest API? Maybe Python could use the C language CredentialProvider?

commits.message:
Update README.md

Now it uses a link to my json api instead of the original

issue.title: Spec no longer executing in geb-example-gradle
issue.body:
## Problem
While playing around with the latest version of the [geb-example-gradle project](https://github.com/geb/geb-example-gradle), I noticed that only the JUnit 4 test was getting run—but the Spock spec was not.

`./gradlew clean chromeTest`

![test results currently](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25108287/190089281-6f1f6b5e-3fe6-45b9-bd19-c993806702a7.png)

## Investigation
I attempted a bisect and it looks like one of the last places where both the JUnit 4 Tests and the Spock Spec both run is commit bfb1fda8e2e0836fd6c143f81f287fbd6f315ef3.

```
git checkout bfb1fda8e2e0836fd6c143f81f287fbd6f315ef3
<adjust chromedriver version>
./gradlew clean chromeTest
```
![test results back then](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25108287/190090066-b0c12c35-a556-471d-8fc9-5a5dcd4b42d4.png)

Anyway, I wanted to help out, so I thought I'd let you know!

comment.body:
Oh, a potentially important detail:
When I try to run specifically that spec on later versions, I get the following:
```
$ ./gradlew clean chromeTest --tests GebishOrgSpec
> Task :chromeTest FAILED

FAILURE: Build failed with an exception.

* What went wrong:
Execution failed for task ':chromeTest'.
> No tests found for given includes: [GebishOrgSpec](--tests filter)
```
